
## Handling audit results

### High-severity vulnerabilities
- **Must be addressed before merging**. Either:
  1. Upgrade to a patched version
  2. Document why the vulnerability doesn't affect this project
- The CI supply-chain job will fail if any high-severity vulnerabilities are found

### Medium/low-severity vulnerabilities
- Review and address as appropriate
- Document any accepted risks in this file

### False positives
- Document in this file with justification
- Consider contributing fixes to `pip-audit` or the vulnerability database

## Version pinning strategy

- Use compatible version ranges in `pyproject.toml` (e.g., `replayt>=0.4.0,<0.5`)
- Pin exact versions only when necessary for security or stability
- Update dependencies regularly to include security patches
- Test with the full Python version matrix (3.11, 3.12) after any dependency change

